commit_message:
Fix scheduler_hints parameter of v3 API

"create a server" API contains a scheduler_hints parameter which is
a hint where a server should boot.
According to scheduler-hints-post-req.json API sample, the parameter
name is "os-scheduler-hints:scheduler_hints":
  {
    "server" : {
      "name" : "new-server-test",
      "image_ref" : "..",
      "flavor_ref" : "..",
      "os-scheduler-hints:scheduler_hints": {
        "hypervisor": "xen",
        "near": "48e6a9f6-30af-47e0-bc04-acaed113bb4e"
      }
    }
  }

However create() of SchedulerHintsController tries to get its value
from invalid position where is the same level as "server":
  {
    "server" : {
      [..]
    },
    "os-scheduler-hints:scheduler_hints": {
      "hypervisor": "xen",
      "near": "48e6a9f6-30af-47e0-bc04-acaed113bb4e"
    }
  }

As the result, Nova cannot get the value from the right parameter.
To fix the problem, this patch merges both the parameter parser and
the validation code to server_create() like the other API extensions.
SchedulerHintsController becomes unnecessary, then this patch removes
the class.

Partially implements bp v3-api-inconsistencies

